  body
    canvas(id='cnvs', with='100%', height='120%', data-processing-sources='/pde/cnvs.pde /hypejs/HYPE.pde') Can't you see the canvas?
    div(id='content', class='container')
      div(id='main')
        h3 <em>Attic</em> is a piece of generative art.
        br
        p It analyses <em>sentiments</em> of tweets marked <a href="https://twitter.com/search?q=%23HavasLofts" target="_blank">#HavasLofts</a> and articles related to the Havas Lofts initiative on <a href="https://medium.com/havas-lofts/" target="_blank">Medium</a>.
        p Based on the emotional valence of their words, it <em>feels</em> the mood of Havas Lofts members.
        br
        p <em>The results of the analysis influence the behaviour of the virtual paintbrush you're painting with.</em>
        br
        p.last Now click anywhere, and move your mouse. Then spread the love.
        a(href="https://twitter.com/share" class="share twitter-share-button" data-text="Attic paints mood using #sentimentanalysis on tweets and blog from #havaslofts" data-via="davypeterbraun" data-count="none" data-hashtags="havaslofts") Tweet
        p(style='clear:both') Go further: check the buttons at the bottom of your screen.

      div(id='tweets-content')
        h3 Tweets data
        br
        p Score: <span id="tweets-data-score">0</span> | Comparative value: <span id="tweets-data-value">0</span><span id="tweets-opinion"></span>
        p The follow terms were captured: <span id='tweets-tokens'></span>

      div(id='medium-content')
        h3 Medium blog posts data
        br
        p Score: <span id="medium-data-score">0</span> | Comparative value: <span id="medium-data-value">0</span> <span id="medium-opinion"></span>
        p The follow terms were captured: <span id='medium-tokens'></span>

      div(id='info')
        p Press "s" to save your painting.
        p <a href="#" id="tweets-data-toggle">Show/hide tweets data</a> | <a href="#" id="medium-data-toggle">Show/hide Medium data</a>

    div(id="save-modal")
      div(id="saved-image-container")
        span
        p Right-click and choose "Save as...". Click outside the image to cancel.